                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="200" height="150">
                    <polygon points="0,150 200,150 100,0" fill="lightgrey" stroke="black" />
                    <polygon points="150,75 50,75 100,150" fill="white" stroke="black" />
                    <polygon points="100,76 123,114 77,114" fill="lightgrey" stroke="black" />
                </svg>

            </image>
            <text>Points D, E, and F are midpoints of the sides of equilateral triangle ABC. The
                shaded central triangle is formed by connecting the midpoints of the sides of
                triangle DEF. What fraction of the total area of ABC is shaded?</text>
        </question>
        <solution>
            <text>Each larger triangle is $\frac{1}{4}$, and smaller triangles are $\frac{1}{4}
                \cdot
                \frac{1}{4}$.

                $\frac{3}{4} + \frac{1}{16} = \frac{13}{16}$</text>
        </solution>
